(Changing size of a circle without moving yet)

To make the circle bigger as we pack more circles 'grow' close together and make a 'bigger circle'
aka ' enlarging the shape'

CODE:


import numpy as np

#generating a random size of a circle (Example values)
radius = random.randrange(3, 40)
x = random.randrange(5, 190)
y = random.randrange(5, 190)

size1 = np.array(radius,x,y)
size2 = np.array(radius,x,y)

#compiling 2 circles in arrays both x and y direction
resize = np.concatenate((size1,size2)) + np.concatenate((size1,size2),axis=1)

